    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The day following Wednesday and preceding Friday, traditionally regarded as the fifth day of the week, but now frequently considered as the fourth. In English and other languages, named for Thor, the Norse god of thunder. In Romance langauges, named for the Roman Jupiter’s-day.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
